tab2=do.call(rbind,lapply(nfvar.list, function(x){
  eval(parse(text=paste('fit<-lm(scale(',x,')~ scale(',xvar,'),X1.dat %>% filter(is.na(',x,')==FALSE & is.na(',xvar,')==FALSE))')))
  tmp=summary(fit)$coefficients
  re=data.frame(yvar=x, xvar=xvar,beta=tmp[,1], CI95=confint(fit),pval=tmp[,4])
  rownames(re)<-NULL
  return(re[2,])
  }))  %>%
  mutate(p.adjust=p.adjust(pval,method='BH'))

sig_pairdtests2 <-function(nname){
  long = nfdata2[, c('Sub.ID','Age',paste('rs.',nname,sep=''),paste('task.',nname,sep=''))] %>%
    melt(.,id=c('Sub.ID','Age')) %>% rename(group=variable) %>%
    arrange(Sub.ID, group)
  long$group = gsub('_wocerebellum','',long$group)
  
  re.table = long %>% 
    t_test(value ~ group, paired = TRUE) %>%
    mutate(.y.=nname) %>%
    add_significance() %>% data.frame(.)
  
  re.fig = ggplot(long, aes(x=group, y=value)) + 
    geom_line(aes(group=Sub.ID,colour=Age),alpha=0.5) + 
#    geom_point() +
    geom_boxplot(alpha=0.5) + 
    # scale_colour_gradientn(colours = rev(rainbow(10,end=0.7))) + 
    scale_colour_gradient(low = "yellow", high = "blue") +
    theme_economist_white(gray_bg = FALSE) +
    stat_compare_means(method = "t.test", paired=TRUE,
                       label.y = 0.17) + 
    ylab("NF") + xlab('') + 
    theme(legend.position="bottom", 
          legend.text=element_text(size=11)) + 
    scale_y_continuous(limits=c(0.05, 0.125), expand = c(0, 0)) + 
    scale_x_discrete(labels = c("Resting", "Task")) + 
    ggtitle(nname)
  
  return(list(re.table, re.fig) )
}

bb=lapply(c('BC','PC'), function(method){
  re=do.call(rbind, lapply(nwlist,function(j){

      melt(.,id='Sub.ID') %>% 
      mutate(variable=factor(variable,levels=paste(j,c('_RS_','_MR_'),method,thresh,sep='')))
    vardesc=tmpdat %>% group_by(variable) %>% summarise(sd = sd(value, na.rm=TRUE)) %>%

    fit=var.test(value ~ variable, tmpdat,alternative="two.sided")

    return(a)
    }))
  row.names(re)<-c()
  return(re)})
